                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1617: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CES1" type="to"
                            >Cunningham</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 16, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. For the Minister. Your March 15, 5 p.m., penultimate sentence. Department
                    approves.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
